data.meta_description: British Monarch. She was the Queen of the United Kingdom and Hanover from June 26, 1830 to June 20, 1837 as consort of King William IV. She was the oldest child of George I, Duke of Saxe-Meiningen and Louisa of Hohenlohe-Langenburg. In a double wedding ceremony with Duke and Duchess of Kent, she married William, Duke...
